<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,342,1322,1348]" pageId="1" pageNumber="410">Host plants.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[349,471,1322,1348]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="410" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Salicaceae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,726,1358,1384]" pageId="1" pageNumber="410" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,818,1637]" box="[199,726,1358,1384]" pageId="1" pageNumber="410">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1358,1384]" pageId="1" pageNumber="410">Distribution.</emphasis>
Palaearctic and Oriental regions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="410" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,818,1637]" pageId="1" pageNumber="410">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1394,1420]" pageId="1" pageNumber="410">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Razowski, J." box="[323,516,1394,1420]" pageId="1" pageNumber="410" pagination="107 - 328" refId="ref6892" refString="Razowski, J. (1989) The genera of Tortricidae (Lepidoptera). Part II: Palaearctic Olethreutinae. Acta Zoologica Cracoviensia, 32 (7), 107 - 328." type="journal article" year="1989">Razowski (1989)</bibRefCitation>
regarded two characters, namely the process of cucullus (pollex) and the form of membrane connecting upper part of basal process of valva, as supposed autapomorphies. However, the latter character was not recognized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kawabe, A. &amp; Nasu, Y." box="[474,742,1466,1493]" pageId="1" pageNumber="410" pagination="79 - 96" refId="ref6249" refString="Kawabe, A. &amp; Nasu, Y. (1994) A revision of the genus Gibberifera Obraztsov (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae), with descriptions of four new species. Tyo to Ga, 45 (2), 79 - 96." type="journal article" year="1994">Kawabe &amp; Nasu (1994)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhang, A. H. &amp; Li, H. H." box="[798,1017,1466,1492]" pageId="1" pageNumber="410" pagination="289 - 295" refId="ref7032" refString="Zhang, A. H. &amp; Li, H. H. (2004) A systematic study on Gibberifera Obraztsov, 1946 from China (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae, Olethreutinae). SHILAP Revista de Lepidopterologia, 32 (128), 289 - 295." type="journal article" year="2004">Zhang &amp; Li (2004)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kawabe, A. &amp; Nasu, Y." box="[1028,1296,1466,1493]" pageId="1" pageNumber="410" pagination="79 - 96" refId="ref6249" refString="Kawabe, A. &amp; Nasu, Y. (1994) A revision of the genus Gibberifera Obraztsov (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae), with descriptions of four new species. Tyo to Ga, 45 (2), 79 - 96." type="journal article" year="1994">Kawabe &amp; Nasu (1994)</bibRefCitation>
put forward two autapomorphies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Obraztsov" authorityYear="1946" box="[422,554,1502,1528]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Gibberifera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[422,554,1502,1528]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="410">Gibberifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, i.e. forewing with a large whitish trapezoidal marking occupying apical 4/5, consisting of a wide median fascia and a large round ocelloid patch and cucullus with a slender process on the ventral angle, bearing a short spine apically, which was supported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhang, A. H. &amp; Li, H. H." box="[883,1099,1574,1600]" pageId="1" pageNumber="410" pagination="289 - 295" refId="ref7032" refString="Zhang, A. H. &amp; Li, H. H. (2004) A systematic study on Gibberifera Obraztsov, 1946 from China (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae, Olethreutinae). SHILAP Revista de Lepidopterologia, 32 (128), 289 - 295." type="journal article" year="2004">Zhang &amp; Li (2004)</bibRefCitation>
. These two characters are also found on the specimens in this study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
